  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong> to a heat proof bowl then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film </strong>and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 5-10 min or until fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673341693113-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673341693113-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673341693113-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673341693113-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1673341693113-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sweet potato cooks, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673341702848-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673341702848-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673341702848-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673341702848-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1673341702848-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>kale</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted kale</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the kale as you can</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673341712234-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673341712234-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673341712234-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673341712234-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1673341712234-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> cooked sweet potato</strong> (careful not to tip any of the water into the pan) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Crush the potatoes lightly and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown</p><p>Tip: Stir as little as possible to give the potatoes a chance to brown</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1673341723543-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1673341723543-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1673341723543-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1673341723543-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1673341723543-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are starting to brown, add your <strong>diced chorizo</strong> to the pan with the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>red onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 6-7 min, stirring occasionally, until the chorizo is cooked through and everything is beginning to crisp</p><p>Tip: Reduce the heat to low if the potatoes start to burn!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1673341729375-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1673341729375-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1673341729375-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1673341729375-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1673341729375-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once everything is beginning to crisp, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan with your<strong> ground paprika</strong> and <strong>ground cumin</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min further until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>wilted kale</strong>, give everything a good mix up and cook for a further 2-3 min or until the kale has softened – this is your <strong>sweet potato & chorizo hash</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1673341739138-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
